---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Pushpaka | AI-Native Multi-Platform Deployment And Monitoring"
  description="Pushpaka is an AI-native self-hosted deployment platform for Docker, Kubernetes, and direct runtime delivery with AI monitoring, AI log analysis, built-in editor workflows, web terminal access, and Traefik-powered routing."
  keywords="Pushpaka, AI deployment platform, self-hosted PaaS, Kubernetes deployment platform, Docker deployment platform, AI monitoring, AI log analyzer, built-in editor, web terminal, Git deployment, Traefik"
>
  <Header />

  <section class="hero-scene pt-36 pb-24 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="hero-grid"></div>
    <div class="hero-glow-orb is-primary"></div>
    <div class="hero-glow-orb is-accent"></div>
    <div class="hero-glow-orb is-field"></div>
    <div class="hero-ring"></div>
    <div class="hero-panel is-tilted"></div>
    <div class="hero-panel is-drifting"></div>

    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid gap-14 lg:grid-cols-[1.2fr_0.8fr] items-center">
        <div>
          <div class="mb-8 inline-block">
            <span class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-brand-950/90 border border-brand-700 rounded-full text-brand-300 text-sm font-medium">
              v1.0.0 · AI-native deployment, monitoring, and operator control
            </span>
          </div>

          <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-bold mb-6 gradient-text leading-tight">
            Deploy everywhere.<br />Scale indefinitely.
          </h1>

          <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-300 mb-10 max-w-3xl">
            Pushpaka is a production-grade self-hosted platform with multi-DB GORM support and a distributed worker engine. Deploy across Docker, remote Vaahan nodes, or direct runtimes with secure Yamux tunneling.
          </p>

          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 mb-12">
            <a href="/install/" class="btn-primary">
              Install v1.0.0
            </a>
            <a href="/features/" class="btn-secondary">
              Explore Shipped Features
            </a>
          </div>

            <div>
              <div class="gradient-text text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Multi-DB</div>
              <div class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Postgres, MySQL, MSSQL, SQL Server, SQLite</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="gradient-text text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Vaahan</div>
              <div class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Distributed serverless execution nodes</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="gradient-text text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Tunnel</div>
              <div class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Secure Yamux reverse multiplexing</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="gradient-text text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Hybrid</div>
              <div class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Remote GORM-backed execution units</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-5">
          <div class="metallic-card p-6">
            <div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-brand-300 mb-3">Operational Flow</div>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-sm text-gray-300">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-accent-400 text-lg">01</span>
                <div>
                  <div class="text-white font-semibold">Connect any Git repository</div>
                  <div>Public or private repos with protected PAT handling, source sync, and operator-friendly project controls.</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-accent-400 text-lg">02</span>
                <div>
                  <div class="text-white font-semibold">Distributed Build & Deploy</div>
                  <div>Distributed execution across Integrated, Vaahan, or Hybrid workers with framework detection and auto-Dockerization.</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-accent-400 text-lg">03</span>
                <div>
                  <div class="text-white font-semibold">Observe and triage with AI</div>
                  <div>Live logs, metrics, health endpoints, worker stats, AI monitoring, and AI log analysis for incident response.</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-accent-400 text-lg">04</span>
                <div>
                  <div class="text-white font-semibold">Edit, route, and recover</div>
                  <div>Built-in editor, terminal access, Traefik domains, TLS, rollback flow, and lifecycle controls in one place.</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="metallic-card p-6">
            <div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-brand-300 mb-3">Operator Surface</div>
            <div class="grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2 text-sm">
              <div class="rounded-xl border border-surface-border bg-slate-950/40 p-4">
                <div class="text-white font-semibold mb-1">Single Binary Dev</div>
                <div class="text-gray-400">`pushpaka -dev` with SQLite, embedded worker, and in-process queue for fast local startup.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-xl border border-surface-border bg-slate-950/40 p-4">
                <div class="text-white font-semibold mb-1">Production Controls</div>
                <div class="text-gray-400">Split API and worker, Docker and Kubernetes controls, editor sync, and terminal workflows.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-28 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent to-brand-950/20">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="section-title gradient-text">Why Pushpaka Wins The Evaluation</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle text-gray-400">The platform already combines deployment, AI-assisted operations, editing, terminal access, and infra control in one operator workflow.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="metallic-card p-8">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-600 to-brand-400 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4 shadow-lg">
            <span class="text-sm font-bold">AI</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">AI Monitoring And Log Analysis</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400">Use AI to monitor failed deployments, inspect alerts, explain logs, chat with deployment context, and bring custom RAG knowledge into triage.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="metallic-card p-8">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-accent-600 to-accent-400 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4 shadow-lg">
            <span class="text-2xl">🚀</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Git Deployments With Rollbacks</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400">Trigger deployments from public or private repositories, stream logs live, track deployment history, and recover fast with rollback workflows.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="metallic-card p-8">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-600 to-cyan-400 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4 shadow-lg">
            <span class="text-2xl">📡</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Enterprise Multi-DB & Distributed Workers</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400">Native GORM support for PG, MySQL, MSSQL, SQL Server, and SQLite. Scale across remote Vaahan (serverless) and Hybrid nodes instantly.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="metallic-card p-8">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-600 to-accent-500 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4 shadow-lg">
            <span class="text-2xl">📡</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Realtime Visibility</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400">WebSocket log streaming, `/health`, `/ready`, `/system`, Prometheus metrics, and worker stats keep operators inside one feedback loop.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="metallic-card p-8">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-600 to-blue-500 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4 shadow-lg">
            <span class="text-2xl">🌐</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Domains, TLS, And Routing</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400">Traefik v3 handles ingress, custom domains, automatic TLS through Let’s Encrypt, and a cleaner self-hosted routing story for production workloads.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="metallic-card p-8">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-600 to-cyan-400 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4 shadow-lg">
            <span class="text-2xl">🚇</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Secure Yamux Tunneling</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400">Connect remote nodes via secure reverse tunnels. Serve web applications from internal networks through your main Pushpaka gateway.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-28 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="section-title gradient-text">Mapped To The Real Product Surface</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle text-gray-400">These areas are already visible in the repository and dashboard code, not just roadmap language.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        <div class="metallic-card p-6">
          <div class="text-brand-300 font-semibold mb-3">AI And Monitoring</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">AI config, monitoring alerts, RAG docs, assistant chat, usage tracking, and deployment log analysis are implemented in backend handlers and services.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metallic-card p-6">
          <div class="text-accent-300 font-semibold mb-3">Editor And Terminal</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">The frontend ships Monaco-based editor flows, while the backend exposes file browsing, save, sync, and terminal WebSocket endpoints.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metallic-card p-6">
          <div class="text-cyan-300 font-semibold mb-3">Multi-Platform Infra</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Docker container controls, Kubernetes resource views, rollout actions, and deploy-target aware project configuration are already wired in the platform.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metallic-card p-6">
          <div class="text-brand-200 font-semibold mb-3">Operator Experience</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Next.js dashboard, Astro docs site, Traefik routing, notifications, OAuth, and deployment workflows combine into one self-hosted control plane.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-28 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="section-title gradient-text">Customer-Facing Value, Not Just Features</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle text-gray-400">Pushpaka is positioned for teams that want a self-hosted platform with AI assistance and operational depth, not another thin deployment wrapper.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="metallic-card p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">For Platform Teams</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400">Consolidate deployment, AI operations, routing, editing, and infrastructure control into one internal platform instead of stitching multiple tools together.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metallic-card p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">For Faster Incident Response</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400">AI monitoring, AI log analysis, metrics, health probes, terminal access, and editor sync reduce the time from alert to fix.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metallic-card p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">For Multi-Environment Delivery</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400">Ship to Docker-backed hosts, Kubernetes-aware targets, or direct runtime environments while keeping one operator workflow and one UI.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metallic-card p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">For Developer Velocity</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400">Built-in editing, terminal access, logs, AI assistance, source sync, and rollback keep teams moving without context-switching across separate products.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-28 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center metallic-card p-12 md:p-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Ship Faster On Infrastructure You Control</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-8 text-lg">Install locally, run a single binary in dev, or ship the full platform with AI-assisted operations, built-in editing, worker separation, and Traefik ingress.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="https://github.com/vikukumar/pushpaka" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn-primary">
          View On GitHub
        </a>
        <a href="/helm-install/" class="btn-secondary">
          Helm Install Guide
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
